I've been to this place several times and the food and service has been good. I have no clue what happened today but it was the strangest experience ever. First we asked the waitress before we sat down if we could sit outside which she just dismissed us and replied that someone is sitting there. Just to clarify, they were not customers, they were random people sitting there because they just got up and left shortly after. Once we sat down, the waitress stood by staring at us and asked us if we were ready to order. We didn't even open the menus yet and she was already asking?? Odd. We order a round of beers and she returned with waters, the beers and a basket of butter bread. Not only did the bread look old but sliced bagels too. What in the fudge?? Once we finally ordered and the food came out, which to me was good as I expected, we found a piece of plastic in the rice. Clearly after that we were done with the food and the "experience". No, I did not bother to tell the waitress because the easiest thing to do is pay and leave and inform others to avoid this place. It is such a shame a nice Spanish restaurant has fallen to such a low since the last time I was there. No bueno

El Viejo Yayo 2 is a smaller establishment than their restaurant on 5th Ave near Barclay's Center. The atmosphere was cozy with small booths towards the back of the room. My friend and I wanted to order paea take out, so we sat at the counter. While we waited latin music was playing in the background. The cuisine was latin typical dishes  ie mofongos, chichaeones, yuca dishes, and drinks like margarita and  coladas. The wait staff was very friendly and several "regulars" came in and chatted with them in either English or Spanish. The  paea was delicious and reasonably priced, loaded with seafood! I would dine at this restaurant again.

At first I ordered pork chop with mushroom. I did gave it a taste and it was salty.  I wasn't able to eat it.  I was with my date and she gave it taste and she too claims it was salty.  Then came the rice that was included with the meal.  That too was soggy and wet not to mention the red beans was watery.  I declared that to the waitress and saw I was right.  Nicely, she was polite and she would gracefully change my course meal.  I ask for bake chicken because I don't eat greasy food.  Well, again the bake chicken was greasy and dripping.  I had no choice but to eat the inside of the chicken.  I don't know what went wrong in the kitchen (maybe it was the cheff) but it seems as if the meal was sitting for so long on the stove.  The only thing i was able to enjoy were the drinks.  You decided whether you want to eat here or not.
